  "text": "The ConfigMap and Secret immutability feature in kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0 is implemented across multiple layers:\n\n## API Layer (Type Definitions)\nThe `Immutable` field is defined in both internal and v1 API types:\n- `pkg/apis/core/types.go:6152-6155` and line 6280-6282 define the Immutable field for ConfigMap and Secret\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go:7396-7399` and 7539-7541 provide v1 API definitions\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/generated.proto:527-534` contains protobuf definitions\n\n## Validation Layer (Immutable Field Validation and Mutation Prevention)\nThe mutation prevention logic prevents data changes when Immutable is set to true:\n- `pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go` contains two critical validation functions:\n  - `ValidateSecretUpdate` (lines 6840-6858): Validates that when `oldSecret.Immutable` is true, the `newSecret.Immutable` must remain true, and the data field cannot be modified\n  - `ValidateConfigMapUpdate` (lines 6897-6916): Similar validation for ConfigMaps, checking that data and binaryData fields cannot be modified when immutable is set\n  - `ValidateImmutableField` (line 362-364): Utility function for field immutability validation\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/validation/objectmeta.go:130-133` provides the base `ValidateImmutableField` implementation used by core validation\n\n## Registry Strategy Layer\nThe strategies enforce validation during API operations:\n- `pkg/registry/core/configmap/strategy.go` implements ConfigMap strategy that calls `validation.ValidateConfigMapUpdate` in its `ValidateUpdate` method (line 87)\n- `pkg/registry/core/secret/strategy.go` implements Secret strategy that calls `validation.ValidateSecretUpdate` in its `ValidateUpdate` method (line 89)\n\n## Watch Optimization Layer (Kubelet Manager)\nThe kubelet uses watch-based managers to skip reflector operations for immutable objects:\n- `pkg/kubelet/util/manager/watch_based_manager.go` provides the core logic:\n  - `objectCacheItem.setImmutable()` (lines 90-94) marks an object as immutable to prevent reflector restart\n  - `objectCache.Get()` (lines 304-352) implements the watch optimization: when an object is retrieved, if it is immutable, the reflector is stopped (lines 343-348) with comment \"Stopped watching for changes - object is immutable\"\n  - `NewWatchBasedManager` (lines 383-400) creates a watch-based manager that accepts an `isImmutable` callback function\n  - `objectCacheItem.stopIfIdle` and `restartReflectorIfNeeded` prevent restarting reflectors for immutable objects (lines 96-118)\n\n- `pkg/kubelet/secret/secret_manager.go` implements the Secret manager:\n  - `NewWatchingSecretManager` (lines 133-159) creates a watch-based secret manager with an immutability check function (lines 149-154) that returns true when `secret.Immutable != nil && *secret.Immutable`\n  - The function passes this check to `manager.NewWatchBasedManager` to enable watch optimization\n\n- `pkg/kubelet/configmap/configmap_manager.go` implements the ConfigMap manager:\n  - `NewWatchingConfigMapManager` (lines 132-158) creates a watch-based configmap manager with an immutability check function (lines 148-153)\n  - Similar pattern to secret manager, checking `configMap.Immutable != nil && *configMap.Immutable`\n\n## Testing\n- `pkg/kubelet/util/manager/watch_based_manager_test.go` contains tests for immutable object behavior:\n  - `TestImmutableSecretStopsTheReflector` (lines 210-313) tests that immutable secrets stop the reflector\n  - `isSecretImmutable` (lines 60-65) test helper function checks the Immutable field\n\n## Apply Configuration\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/applyconfigurations/core/v1/secret.go:249-251` provides `WithImmutable` setter for apply configuration\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/applyconfigurations/core/v1/configmap.go:248-250` provides `WithImmutable` setter for ConfigMap apply configuration\n\n## Implementation Chain\nThe feature works through a coordinated chain: When a pod references an immutable Secret or ConfigMap, the watch-based manager (initialized via `NewWatchingSecretManager` or `NewWatchingConfigMapManager`) starts a reflector to monitor the object. Upon the first `GetObject()` call, if the object has `Immutable=true`, the reflector is immediately stopped via `item.setImmutable()` and `item.stop()`, eliminating unnecessary watch operations for data that cannot change. The API layer prevents mutation attempts via validation in `ValidateConfigMapUpdate` and `ValidateSecretUpdate`, which enforce that when `Immutable` is true, neither the immutable flag nor the data fields can be modified."
}

